# Interactive Checklist Component

This is a demonstration of the powerful Checklist component for MDX. It features nested items, progress tracking, localStorage persistence, and export functionality.

## Basic Checklist

Here's a simple checklist with a few items:

<Checklist
  title="Getting Started Tasks"
  items={[
    { id: '1', text: 'Install dependencies', checked: false },
    { id: '2', text: 'Set up development environment', checked: false },
    { id: '3', text: 'Run the development server', checked: false },
  ]}
  storageKey="basic-checklist"
/>

## Nested Checklist with Subitems

This example demonstrates nested items with two levels of hierarchy:

<Checklist
  title="Project Setup Checklist"
  storageKey="project-setup-checklist"
  showProgress={true}
  allowExport={true}
  items={[
    {
      id: 'setup-1',
      text: 'Initial Setup',
      checked: false,
      subitems: [
        { id: 'setup-1-1', text: 'Clone repository', checked: false },
        { id: 'setup-1-2', text: 'Install Node.js', checked: false },
        { id: 'setup-1-3', text: 'Install dependencies', checked: false },
      ]
    },
    {
      id: 'setup-2',
      text: 'Configuration',
      checked: false,
      subitems: [
        { id: 'setup-2-1', text: 'Set up environment variables', checked: false },
        { id: 'setup-2-2', text: 'Configure database', checked: false },
        { id: 'setup-2-3', text: 'Set up authentication', checked: false },
      ]
    },
    {
      id: 'setup-3',
      text: 'Development',
      checked: false,
      subitems: [
        { id: 'setup-3-1', text: 'Create feature branch', checked: false },
        { id: 'setup-3-2', text: 'Set up linting and formatting', checked: false },
        { id: 'setup-3-3', text: 'Configure testing', checked: false },
      ]
    },
    {
      id: 'setup-4',
      text: 'Deployment',
      checked: false,
      subitems: [
        { id: 'setup-4-1', text: 'Set up CI/CD pipeline', checked: false },
        { id: 'setup-4-2', text: 'Configure production environment', checked: false },
        { id: 'setup-4-3', text: 'Deploy to production', checked: false },
      ]
    }
  ]}
/>

## Features

### Progress Tracking

The checklist automatically calculates and displays progress based on all items (including subitems). The progress bar shows:
- Completion percentage
- Visual progress bar with gradient
- Count of completed vs total items

### LocalStorage Persistence

Checklist state is automatically saved to localStorage when a `storageKey` is provided. This means:
- Progress is preserved across page refreshes
- Users can close and return to the page later
- Multiple checklists can have unique storage keys

### Bulk Actions

Click the menu button (⋮) in the top-right to access:
- **Check All**: Mark all items as complete
- **Uncheck All**: Mark all items as incomplete
- **Reset**: Reset to initial state (clears localStorage)
- **Export as Markdown**: Download the checklist as a .md file

### Nested Items

Support for two levels of hierarchy:
- Parent items with subitems
- Visual connector lines showing hierarchy
- Parent items auto-check when all subitems are complete

### Keyboard Accessibility

- Navigate with Tab key
- Toggle checkboxes with Space or Enter
- Full ARIA attributes for screen readers

### Styling

The component features:
- Custom styled checkboxes (not browser default)
- 20x20px rounded checkboxes with 4px border radius
- Terracotta (#E07A5F) accent color for checked state
- Strikethrough text for completed items
- Smooth transitions and hover effects
- Dark mode support

## Usage Example

```tsx

<Checklist
  title="My Checklist"
  storageKey="my-checklist"
  showProgress={true}
  allowExport={true}
  items={[
    {
      id: '1',
      text: 'Main item',
      checked: false,
      subitems: [
        { id: '1-1', text: 'Subitem 1', checked: false },
        { id: '1-2', text: 'Subitem 2', checked: false },
      ]
    },
    {
      id: '2',
      text: 'Another item',
      checked: true,
    }
  ]}
/>
```

## Try It Out

Interact with the checklists above to see the features in action:
- Click checkboxes to toggle items
- Watch the progress bar update
- Refresh the page to see localStorage persistence
- Use the menu to check/uncheck all items
- Export your checklist as Markdown
